description: From Middle Dutch fletsen (“to flatter, fawn”). More at flatter.

verbs.description: fleech (third-person singular simple present fleeches, present participle fleeching, simple past and past participle fleeched)

entries.meaning: (transitive, Scotland) To wheedle; coax; cajole; induce with fair words; flatter.
(intransitive, Scotland) To use cajoling or flattering words; speak insincerely.
